title: Define Keyword: Data Analyst
text: Before diving into the problem, let's clarify who a "Data Analyst" is. A data analyst is responsible for collecting, processing, and performing statistical analyses on large datasets. They make sense of data to help companies make informed decisions.

title: Define Keyword: Processing
text: The term "processing," in the context of data, refers to actions performed on raw data to convert it into a meaningful format that can be analyzed or used for decision-making.

title: Dependency Keyword: Visualizing
text: "Visualizing" involves creating visual representations of data, like graphs or charts, to make it easier to understand patterns, trends, and insights.

title: Dependency Keyword: Reporting
text: "Reporting," in a business context, usually involves compiling and presenting data findings with an emphasis on putting them into a narrative that aids in decision-making.
